The paper deals with feature extraction and dimensionality reduction, which are common topics in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of "nonlinear data correlations" and "discriminative analytics" suggests a potential focus on neural networks or other nonlinear models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
